author: Adam Jude
title: Huskies get recruiting commitment from Phoenix quarterback Daniel Bridge-Gadd
text:
Huskies get recruiting commitment from Phoenix quarterback Daniel Bridge-Gadd Originally published October 19, 2015 at 3:51 pm Daniel Bridge-Gadd was previously committed to New Mexico State. By Adam Jude Seattle Times staff reporter 
Daniel Bridge-Gadd , a 6-foot-2, 201-pound quarterback from Paradise Valley High in Phoenix, made a verbal commitment to the Huskies on Monday, Scout reports. 
Bridge-Gadd was one of about 10 recruits who visit UW over the weekend. 
He was previously committed to New Mexico State. He is rated a two-star recruit by Scout and a three-star recruit by 247sports.com.
